mit shape universality,\" in the sense of Levine and Peres,\namong the four Laplacian growth models: divisible sandpiles, abelian sandpiles,\nrotor-router aggregation, and internal diffusion-limited aggregation (IDLA). We\nconclude the paper with conjectures about radial fluctuations in IDLA on $SG$,\npossible extensions of limit shape universality to other state spaces, and\nrelated open problems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Jul 2018 17:55:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Sep 2018 08:45:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 19 Jun 2019 13:13:53 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 5 Aug 2019 00:44:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
