, it can reproduce with very good agreement the quasinormal ringdown\nas well as with rather good agreement the tail of the signal. This is achieved\neven if we take into account only one Regge pole and, if a large number of\nmodes are excited, the result can be improved by considering additional poles.\nMoreover, while quasinormal-mode contributions do not provide physically\nrelevant results at \"early times\" due to their exponentially divergent behavior\nas time decreases, it is not necessary to determine from physical\nconsiderations a starting time for the Regge ringdown.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Jul 2018 12:02:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Sep 2018 14:10:57 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 27 Sep 2018 11:50:35 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 15 Apr 2020 18:13:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-17"}
