ion and we construct this solution with the help\nof a marked Brownian coalescent point process. When $\\psi(x)=x^\\gamma$, we show\nthe existence of a self-similar solution for the PDE which relates when\n$\\gamma=2$ to the speed of coming down from infinity of the nested Kingman\ncoalescent.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Jul 2018 14:38:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-25"}
